   \"stateDataBehavior\": [\n980:         \"Detail screen consumes selected restaurant and menu/cart streams from shared repository state.\",\n981:         \"Recommended, non-veg, and veg sections preserve independent expansion state.\",\n982:         \"Like toggle updates visible state immediately.\",\n983:         \"Cart page filters out zero-count items and keeps summary sections visible.\"\n984:       ],\n985:       \"deferredRisks\": [\n986:         \"Source cart increment/decrement callbacks are placeholders; target needs a documented parity decision on mutation depth.\",\n987:         \"Share action remains placeholder unless product specifies outbound sharing UX.\"\n988:       ],\n989:       \"implementationGroups\": [\n990:         {\n991:           \"groupId\": \"phase-05-detail-state-and-sections\",\n992:           \"title\": \"Detail state, menu grouping, and toggles\",\n993:           \"groupType\": \"source-behavior\",\n994:           \"priority\": \"critical\",\n995:           \"sourcePaths\": [\n996:             \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/details/RestaurantDetail.kt\",\n997:             \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/details/RestaurantDetailViewModel.kt\",\n998:             \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/details/DetailScreenState.kt\",\n999:             \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/details/components/*.kt\",\n1000:             \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/data/repository/UserDataRepositoryImpl.kt\"\n1001:           ],\n1002:           \"sourceMethods\": [\n1003:             \"RestaurantDetail\",\n1004:             \"RestaurantDetailViewModel.onEvent\",\n1005:             \"getSavedRestaurant\",\n1006:             \"getMenuItems\",\n1007:             \"isRestaurantLiked\"\n1008:           ],\n1009:           \"featureIds\": [\n1010:             \"app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-presentation-detai-958b17f285-005-observable-state-viewmodel-flow-livedata\",\n1011:             \"app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-presentation-detai-017392d1f5-003-navigation-surface-menu-drawer-toolbar-o\"\n1012:           ],\n1013:           \"resourceInputs\": [\n1014:             \"recommended\",\n1015:             \"non_vegetarian\",\n1016:             \"vegetarian\",\n1017:             \"drop_down_arrow\",\n1018:             \"share\",\n1019:             \"cart\"\n1020:           ],\n1021:           \"platformCapabilityIds\": [\n1022:             \"image-viewer-gestures\",\n1023:             \"file-access-and-saf\"\n1024:           ],\n1025:           \"uiContracts\": [\n1026:             \"back action plus like/share actions\",\n1027:             \"restaurant card followed by expandable menu sections\",\n1028:             \"floating cart action when menu count sum is non-zero\"\n1029:           ],\n1030:           \"dataContracts\": [\n1031:             \"DetailScreenState.restaurant\",\n1032:             \"DetailScreenState.recommendedExpandedState\",\n1033:             \"DetailScreenState.nonVegExpandedState\",\n1034:             \"DetailScreenState.vegExpandedState\",\n1035:             \"DetailScreenState.menuList\",\n1036:             \"DetailScreenState.recommendedList\",\n1037:             \"DetailScreenState.isLiked\"\n1038:           ],\n1039:           \"expectedTargetDomains\": [\n1040:             \"features/detail\",\n1041:             \"data/session\"\n1042:           ],\n1043:           \"requiredBehaviors\": [\n1044:             \"Menu list partitions into recommended, veg, and non-veg views.\",\n1045:             \"Expansion toggles update immediately without leaving the page.\",\n1046:             \"Selected restaurant details render from shared state rather than route-only stubs.\"\n1047:           ],\n1048:           \"riskHints\": [\n1049:             \"Seed may overstate file access/image viewer capability from static resource usage; confirm before closing capability rows.\"\n1050:           ],\n1051:           \"acceptanceEvidence\": [\n1052:             \"focused detail/cart state tests\",\n1053:             \"build gate pass\"\n1054:           ]\n1055:         },\n1056:         {\n1057:           \"groupId\": \"phase-05-cart-summary-and-mutations\",\n1058:           \"title\": \"Cart summary and mutation surfaces\",\n1059:           \"groupType\": \"source-behavior\",\n1060:           \"priority\": \"high\",\n1061:           \"sourcePaths\": [\n1062:             \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/cart/Cart.kt\",\n1063:             \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/cart/CartViewModel.kt\",\n1064:             \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/cart/CartState.kt\",\n1065:             \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/cart/components/*.kt\"\n1066:           ],\n1067:           \"sourceMethods\": [\n1068:             \"Cart\"\n1069:           ],\n1070:           \"featureIds\": [],\n1071:           \"resourceInputs\": [\n1072:             \"back\",\n1073:             \"add\",\n1074:             \"subtract\",\n1075:             \"cart\"\n1076:           ],\n1077:           \"platformCapabilityIds\": [],\n1078:           \"uiContracts\": [\n1079:             \"close/back affordance\",\n1080:             \"item list, coupon bar, delivery section, bill section\"\n1081:           ],\n1082:           \"dataContracts\": [\n1083:             \"CartState.list\"\n1084:           ],\n1085:           \"expectedTargetDomains\": [\n1086:             \"features/cart\",\n1087:             \"data/session\"\n1088:           ],\n1089:           \"requiredBehaviors\": [\n1090:             \"Zero-count items are hidden from the rendered list.\",\n1091:             \"Coupon, delivery, and bill sections remain visible.\",\n1092:             \"Mutation affordances must not be silently removed even if source callbacks are placeholders.\"\n1093:           ],\n1094:           \"riskHints\": [\n1095:             \"Source cart mutation callbacks are empty; parity may require a small clarified target behavior rather than no-op buttons hidden from UI.\"\n1096:           ],\n1097:           \"acceptanceEvidence\": [\n1098:             \"focused detail/cart state tests\",\n1099:             \"manual review of cart page\"\n1100:           ]\n1101:         }\n1102:       ]\n1103:     },\n1104:     {\n1105:       \"id\": \"phase-06-profile-capabilities-verification\",\n1106:       \"title\": \"Profile, capability resolution, and verification hardening\",\n1107:       \"priority\": \"high\",\n1108:       \"targetScope\": [\n1109:         \"Migrate profile/logout flow and document placeholder profile actions.\",\n1110:         \"Resolve or explicitly defer remaining platform capabilities with evidence.\",\n1111:         \"Add focused target verification for core state and data behavior.\"\n1112:       ],\n1113:       \"sourceEvidence\": [\n1114:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/profile/Profile.kt\",\n1115:         \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/profile/ProfileViewModel.kt\",\n1116:         \"app/src/test/java/com/example/foodike/ExampleUnitTest.kt\",\n1117:         \"app/src/androidTest/java/com/example/foodike/ExampleInstrumentedTest.kt\",\n1118:         \"translation-inputs/platform-capability-check.json\",\n1119:         \"translation-inputs/coverage-gap-report.md\"\n1120:       ],\n1121:       \"requiredInputs\": [\n1122:         \"translation-inputs/platform-capability-check.json\",\n1123:         \"translation-inputs/source-coverage-matrix.json\",\n1124:         \"translation-inputs/verification-results.json\"\n1125:       ],\n1126:       \"expectedFiles\": [\n1127:         \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/profile\",\n1128:         \"entry/src/test\",\n1129:         \"plan.md\",\n1130:         \"plan.json\"\n1131:       ],\n1132:       \"gateCommand\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\Sieger\\\\AppData\\\\Local\\\\Programs\\\\Python\\\\Python312\\\\python.exe D:\\\\X2Cangjie\\\\X2Cangjie\\\\scripts\\\\shared\\\\reports\\\\build_hap_report.py --workspace-root D:\\\\workspace\\\\Foodike --target-project D:\\\\workspace\\\\Foodike\\\\Foodike-Harmony --phase phase-06-profile-capabilities-verification\",\n1133:       \"expectedTests\": [\n1134:         \"cjpm test\",\n1135:         \"manual profile/logout smoke review if device available\"\n1136:       ],\n1137:       \"stateDataBehavior\": [\n1138:         \"Logout must clear session path and return to onboarding-style entry.\",\n1139:         \"Focused tests must cover startup/session/repository/detail helper logic rather than placeholder package checks only.\"\n1140:       ],\n1141:       \"deferredRisks\": [\n1142:         \"Capability rows for file/media/permissions may end as source overrides or deferred depending on confirmed source behavior and HarmonyOS callable APIs.\",\n1143:         \"If target test harness cannot run, exact blocker must be recorded and behavior proof must rely on compile/manual evidence plus pure-module tests.\"\n1144:       ],\n1145:       \"implementationGroups\": [\n1146:         {\n1147:           \"groupId\": \"phase-06-profile-and-logout\",\n1148:           \"title\": \"Profile page and logout flow\",\n1149:           \"groupType\": \"source-behavior\",\n1150:           \"priority\": \"high\",\n1151:           \"sourcePaths\": [\n1152:             \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/profile/Profile.kt\",\n1153:             \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/profile/ProfileViewModel.kt\",\n1154:             \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/profile/components/ProfileCard.kt\"\n1155:           ],\n1156:           \"sourceMethods\": [\n1157:             \"Profile\",\n1158:             \"ProfileViewModel.onEvent\"\n1159:           ],\n1160:           \"featureIds\": [\n1161:             \"app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-presentation-profi-e492afed0c-004-observable-state-viewmodel-flow-livedata\",\n1162:             \"app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-presentation-profi-c34aae0a57-002-navigation-surface-menu-drawer-toolbar-o\"\n1163:           ],\n1164:           \"resourceInputs\": [\n1165:             \"display_picture\",\n1166:             \"edit\",\n1167:             \"saved_addresses\",\n1168:             \"payments_and_refunds\",\n1169:             \"online_ordering_help\",\n1170:             \"about\",\n1171:             \"log_out\"\n1172:           ],\n1173:           \"platformCapabilityIds\": [],\n1174:           \"uiContracts\": [\n1175:             \"profile summary, profile cards, logout button\"\n1176:           ],\n1177:           \"dataContracts\": [\n1178:             \"logout callback to session store\"\n1179:           ],\n1180:           \"expectedTargetDomains\": [\n1181:             \"features/profile\",\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 1-1181. Use offset=1182 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\n      \"targetPath\": \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/bootstrap_page.cj\",\n      \"sourceReferences\": [\n        \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/MainActivity.kt\",\n        \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/util/Navigation.kt\"\n      ],\n      \"topLevelDefinitions\": [\n        \"bootstrap page shell\",\n        \"root route composition\"\n      ],\n      \"translationGuidelines\": [\n        \"Keep this file as a shell that delegates to feature modules.\",\n        \"Do not absorb repository or screen-specific logic here.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"targetPath\": \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/app_router.cj\",\n      \"sourceReferences\": [","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"plan.json","time":{"start":1782532461179,"end":1782532461184}},"id":"prt_f0736d266001ZmU3wVOFLJvrHI","sessionID":"ses_0f8c95b2bffeQwsbU7G0I8nx6k","messageID":"msg_f0736c3b6001aCb6DxfGqYVvPM"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532461256,"sessionID":"ses_0f8c95b2bffeQwsbU7G0I8nx6k","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_06Wo2Zf4XUvc7Q8hagosQwIn","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"D:\\X2Cangjie\\X2Cangjie\\docs\\harmonyos-cangjie-translation-checklist.md"},"output":"<path>D:\\X2Cangjie\\X2Cangjie\\docs\\harmonyos-cangjie-translation-checklist.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # HarmonyOS Cangjie Translation Checklist\n2: \n3: 面向 Android Java app 迁移到 HarmonyOS Cangjie 的阶段性检查表。它来自 Spendee 案例记录和后续构建修复经验，目标是在每个 `opencode-cj` phase 结束时先抓住高频编译/宏展开问题，再进入下一阶段。\n4: \n5: ## 使用时机\n6: \n7: 1. 每个翻译 phase 开始前，把本 phase 可能触及的条目加入 `opencode-cj` prompt。\n8: 2. 每个 phase 结束后，先运行完整构建门禁：\n9: \n10:    `<python>` 表示当前 Python 解释器：macOS/Linux 可用 `python3`，Windows 可用 `py -3` 或 `python`。\n11: \n12:    ```bash\n13:    <python> scripts/shared/reports/build_hap_report.py \\\n14:      --workspace-root <translation-workspace> \\\n15:      --target-project <target-project> \\\n16:      --phase <phase-name>\n17:    ```\n18: \n19: 3. 如果报告失败，把 `build-reports/<phase-name>/build-report.md` 和首个 blocker 交给 `opencode-cj` 修复当前 phase，不要先开启下一阶段。\n20: 4. 构建通过后，再进入运行时 smoke 或行为验证。\n21: \n22: ## 资源和字符串边界\n23: \n24: - 不要把 `@r(...)` / `AppResource` 直接当作普通 `String`。\n25: - UI prop 如果可能接收资源字符串，优先使用 `ResourceStr`，或在边界处做 SDK 支持的显式转换。\n26: - 不要对 `ResourceStr` 调用普通字符串方法，例如 `isEmpty()`；需要空态时使用独立 `Bool` 状态。\n27: - 迁移 Android `setText(...)` 时，确认 HarmonyOS 端有明确的状态赋值或可观察数据源驱动文本刷新。\n28: - 每次资源迁移后，检查 `string.json`、media 资源和实际 UI 引用，避免保留旧 placeholder key 或缺失 AppScope/entry 双层资源。\n29: \n30: ## Option 和控制流\n31: \n32: - 不要生成 Java/Kotlin 风格的 `Option.get()`。\n33: - 非 UI helper 中使用 `match`、显式 `case Some(...)` / `case None`，或当前 SDK 支持的安全访问 API。\n34: - UI 构建逻辑中避免直接让 `match` 分支裸露生成不兼容的 component 形态；需要时拆成命名 `@Builder`。\n35: - 启动/依赖注入状态建议拆成明确的 `Bool`、错误资源、服务 option 解包 helper，减少 `@Component` 宏失败面。\n36: \n37: ## 包结构和导入\n38: \n39: - 避免 root package 与 `pages` / `routing` 之间出现环形依赖。公共 route 类型优先放在 `routing` 或独立 models/helpers 包。\n40: - UI 文件中避免宽泛 `std.collection.*` 导入；它可能和 ArkUI 组件名冲突，例如 `Stack`。\n41: - 需要集合类型时优先显式导入或限定命名。\n42: - helper 类型如果会通过 public `@Component` 生成构造器暴露，确认类型本身也是必要的 public 可见性。\n43: - 不要把临时 template/cache 文件当成迁移输入；`.cache`、build output 和 diagnostic log 只作为诊断证据。\n44: \n45: ## ArkUI Component 和 Builder\n46: \n47: - `@BuilderParam` 优先传入命名 `@Builder` 方法，不要依赖未验证的 inline closure 或 trailing component block。\n48: - 自定义容器组件要按当前 SDK 支持的构造器/slot 形态实现，不能照搬 ArkTS 示例。\n49: - 校验 ArkUI named arguments 和 modifiers 来自当前 Cangjie HarmonyOS SDK 文档，而不是只参考 ArkTS。\n50: - 对 `@Component` macro 失败，先缩小到入口组件状态、构造器 public 类型、资源字符串类型和 `@Publish` 字段类型这四类高频根因。\n51: - 组件内部紧密相关的 owner state 文本可直接在 owning page builder 中渲染，避免子组件 prop 复用导致同会话文本不刷新。\n52: \n53: ## 状态和可观察集合\n54: \n55: - 路由和跨页面状态模型使用 SDK 支持的 `@Observed`、`@Publish` 和明确字段类型。\n56: - 需要列表变化驱动 UI 时，使用 `ObservedArrayList` 等 SDK 支持的数据源，并给 `ForEach` 提供稳定 key。\n57: - 不要假设 `ObservedArrayList` 是普通 iterator；辅助逻辑中用下标访问或 SDK 支持方法。\n58: - 跨组件变化的 prop 需要 `@Prop` / `@Link` / `@Watch` 等明确同步链路。\n59: - 对 primitive totals、余额、计数等关键展示值，保存/编辑/删除成功后优先执行明确赋值，避免只依赖持久化回读触发 UI。\n60: \n61: ## 测试迁移和验证\n62: \n63: - 源项目已有测试时，当前 phase 相关测试应迁移或改写为目标侧测试，验证翻译后的业务、数据、状态、资源或刷新行为。\n64: - 源项目没有测试时，应为核心可测试逻辑补充适量测试；源测试过少时，应优先补高风险行为测试。\n65: - 如果当前 SDK/模板不支持某类自动化测试，应保持代码可测试，并记录 deferred validation、替代验证方法和后续完成路径。\n66: - 不要为了通过构建直接删除、禁用或弱化已迁移/生成的测试；应修实现、修测试集成，或明确记录当前阶段测试限制。\n67: \n68: ## 构建配置和工具链\n69: \n70: - 完整 HAP 构建必须使用 DevEco Cangjie plugin 管理的 full SDK，例如 `~/.cangjie-sdk/<version>/cangjie`；standalone `~/.local/cangjie` 只能代表轻量 `cjc` / `cjpm` 可用。\n71: - 缺少 full SDK 时，应先安装/启用 DevEco Studio Cangjie plugin，再继续 full build gate。\n72: - 每阶段记录构建命令、失败阶段、首个 blocker 和已解决 blocker。\n73: - 常见阶段含义：\n74:   - `ohpm install`：依赖、registry、模板测试依赖或 oh-package 问题。\n75:   - `SyncCangjieResource`：资源生成、配置 schema、Cangjie build support 注入问题。\n76:   - `CompileCangjie`：Cangjie 语法、宏展开、包依赖、ArkUI API 问题。\n77:   - `PackageHap`：资源/loader/package 产物问题。\n78:   - `SignHap`：签名配置问题；未签名 debug HAP 通常可能只是 warning。\n79: - full build 通过前，不要把 standalone `cjpm check` 失败简单等同于 HAP 构建失败；两者依赖来源不同。\n80: \n81: ## opencode-cj 修复交接\n82: \n83: - `apply_patch` 失败后必须 read-back，因为失败可能部分落盘。\n84: - `L.map is not a function`、`apply_patch verification failed`、`Failed to read file to update` 要分开记录。\n85: - 长 phase 被打断或恢复时，先让 `opencode-cj` 检查文件系统当前状态，再继续，不要重复生成同名组件或服务。\n86: - 构建 blocker prompt 应包含：\n87:   - 当前 phase 名称。\n88:   - `build-report.md` 路径。\n89:   - 失败阶段。\n90:   - 首个 blocker message 和 location。\n91:   - 只修当前 phase blocker 的约束。\n92: \n93: ## Phase Gate 验收\n94: \n95: - `build_hap_report.py` 的 Markdown/JSON 报告存在。\n96: - 报告包含 command、result、failed stage、first blocker、warnings、HAP artifacts。\n97: - 如果失败，已有 `opencode-build-blocker-prompt.txt` 可直接交给 `opencode-cj`。\n98: - 如果成功，报告记录 full build gate 通过，且可把本 phase 的已知编译 blocker 标为 resolved。\n99: - 下一 phase 只能在构建通过，或用户明确批准带 blocker 继续时开始。\n100: \n101: ## Spendee 证据映射\n102: \n103: - `@r(...)` / `ResourceStr` 误用导致重复 generic inference 和 macro blocker。\n104: - `Option.get()` 在当前 SDK 下不可用，入口和服务解包需改为显式 `match`。\n105: - root/pages/routing 包循环会阻断 `CompileCangjie`。\n106: - UI 文件中的 `std.collection.*` 与 ArkUI `Stack` 名称冲突。\n107: - `@BuilderParam` 命名 builder 比 inline closure 更稳定。\n108: - `ObservedArrayList` 不能按普通 `for-in` 假设处理。\n109: - 同会话 finance totals 刷新最终需要 owner state、显式赋值和可观察列表配合，构建通过不能替代运行时刷新验证。\n110: - 如果 full SDK 在 Phase 1 就接入，许多 Cangjie/ArkUI 编译问题可以在引入当 phase 就暴露，而不是累积到最终构建。\n\n(End of file - total 110 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# HarmonyOS Cangjie Translation Checklist\n\n面向 Android Java app 迁移到 HarmonyOS Cangjie 的阶段性检查表。它来自 Spendee 案例记录和后续构建修复经验，目标是在每个 `opencode-cj` phase 结束时先抓住高频编译/宏展开问题，再进入下一阶段。\n\n## 使用时机\n\n1. 每个翻译 phase 开始前，把本 phase 可能触及的条目加入 `opencode-cj` prompt。\n2. 每个 phase 结束后，先运行完整构建门禁：\n\n   `<python>` 表示当前 Python 解释器：macOS/Linux 可用 `python3`，Windows 可用 `py -3` 或 `python`。\n\n   ```bash\n   <python> scripts/shared/reports/build_hap_report.py \\\n     --workspace-root <translation-workspace> \\\n     --target-project <target-project> \\\n     --phase <phase-name>\n   ```\n\n3. 如果报告失败，把 `build-reports/<phase-name>/build-report.md` 和首个 blocker 交给 `opencode-cj` 修复当前 phase，不要先开启下一阶段。\n4. 构建通过后，再进入运行时 smoke 或行为验证。","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"..\\..\\X2Cangjie\\X2Cangjie\\docs\\harmonyos-cangjie-translation-checklist.md","time":{"start":1782532461247,"end":1782532461255}},"id":"prt_f0736d27c001ava99yEul3Wj9L","sessionID":"ses_0f8c95b2bffeQwsbU7G0I8nx6k","messageID":"msg_f0736c3b6001aCb6DxfGqYVvPM"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532461272,"sessionID":"ses_0f8c95b2bffeQwsbU7G0I8nx6k","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Pib25b4tZcl5pPp4woBoAMV0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\phase-task-checklist.md"},"output":"<path>D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\phase-task-checklist.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Phase Task Checklist\n2: \n3: - Phase: `phase-01-project-skeleton-resources`\n4: \n5: ## Purpose\n6: \n7: Current-phase task checklist generated from the agent-maintained source coverage matrix and platform capability check. Use it before editing and update the matrix/check after work.\n8: \n9: ## Summary\n10: \n11: | metric | value |\n12: | --- | --- |\n13: | phaseFeatureEntries | 49 |\n14: | phaseCriticalHighFeatureEntries | 44 |\n15: | mustCompleteFeatureEntries | 28 |\n16: | needsEvidenceFeatureEntries | 0 |\n17: | deferredOrFallbackFeatureEntries | 3 |\n18: | coveredFeatureEntries | 13 |\n19: | phaseSourceFiles | 19 |\n20: | phasePlatformCapabilityEntries | 1 |\n21: | phaseCriticalHighPlatformCapabilityEntries | 1 |\n22: | mustCompletePlatformCapabilityEntries | 0 |\n23: | needsEvidencePlatformCapabilityEntries | 0 |\n24: | implementationGroups | 13 |\n25: | planContractAvailable | True |\n26: | planContractMatchedGroups | 1 |\n27: | planContractUnmatchedGroups | 0 |\n28: | implementationGroupSourceBehavior | 8 |\n29: | implementationGroupResourceMigration | 2 |\n30: | implementationGroupPlatformCapability | 1 |\n31: | implementationGroupVerification | 1 |\n32: | implementationGroupArchitectureRisk | 1 |\n33: | implementationGroupUiContracts | 1 |\n34: | behaviorAuditFeatureContracts | 44 |\n35: | behaviorAuditOpenFeatureContracts | 0 |\n36: | behaviorAuditPlatformContracts | 1 |\n37: | testHarnessReportAvailable | False |\n38: | testHarnessAcceptedPass | False |\n39: | unassignedCriticalHighFeatureEntries | 0 |\n40: | unassignedCriticalHighPlatformCapabilityEntries | 0 |\n41: \n42: ## Feature Status Counts\n43: \n44: | status | count |\n45: | --- | --- |\n46: | implemented | 1 |\n47: | not-applicable | 3 |\n48: | planned | 33 |\n49: | platform-replaced | 12 |\n50: \n51: ## Platform Capability Status Counts\n52: \n53: | status | count |\n54: | --- | --- |\n55: | verified-direct | 1 |\n56: \n57: ## Plan Contract Alignment\n58: \n59: Use this section as upstream planning ownership evidence. If it conflicts with source code, source-coverage-matrix.json, or platform-capability-check.json, resolve the authority records or document an analysis gap/source override before closing the phase.\n60: \n61: ### Matched Plan Groups\n62: \n63: | group id | type | priority | matched generated groups | source paths | features | capabilities | risks |\n64: | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n65: | phase-01-route-shell-and-resource-baseline | source-behavior | critical | phase-01-project-skeleton-resources-resource-migration-manifest, phase-01-project-skeleton-resources-resource-migration-res-values, phase-01-project-skeleton-resources-source-behavior-presentation-util | app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml, app/src/main/res/values/strings.xml, app/src/main/res/values/colors.xml |  | localization-resources | Current target string coverage is only partial.; Target shell concentration already exists in bootstrap_page.cj. |\n66: \n67: ## Behavior Audit\n68: \n69: | metric | value |\n70: | --- | --- |\n71: | featureContracts | 44 |\n72: | openFeatureContracts | 0 |\n73: | platformContracts | 1 |\n74: \n75: ### Behavior Audit Feature Status Counts\n76: \n77: | status | count |\n78: | --- | --- |\n79: | implemented | 1 |\n80: | not-applicable | 3 |\n81: | planned | 28 |\n82: | platform-replaced | 12 |\n83: \n84: ### Behavior Audit Parity Counts\n85: \n86: | parity | count |\n87: | --- | --- |\n88: | equivalent | 1 |\n89: | not-applicable | 3 |\n90: | platform-replaced | 12 |\n91: | unverified | 28 |\n92: \n93: ### Open Feature Contracts\n94: \n95: _No open current-phase feature contracts._\n96: \n97: ### Feature Contracts\n98: \n99: | feature id | importance | status | parity | source path | target behavior |\n100: | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n101: | app-build-gradle-kts-ab52d0a44d-001-navigation-surface-menu-drawer-toolbar-o | critical | platform-replaced | platform-replaced | app/build.gradle.kts | HarmonyOS replaces Navigation Compose with a route shell in app_router.cj and bootstrap_page.cj, with the entry page registered in main_pages.json. |\n102: | app-build-gradle-kts-329cf39b55-002-runtime-permission-request-permission-re | critical | not-applicable | not-applicable | app/build.gradle.kts | HarmonyOS phase-01 build configuration likewise declares no permission-specific module wiring and keeps requestPermissions empty. |\n103: | app-build-gradle-kts-52a26dc1e9-003-android-platform-component-lifecycle-suc | critical | platform-replaced | platform-replaced | app/build.gradle.kts | HarmonyOS replaces the Android Gradle application stack with entry/build-profile.json5, entry/cjpm.toml, module.json5, and EntryAbility/FoodikeAbilityStage lifecycle registration. |\n104: | app-build-gradle-kts-0a842e752f-004-screen-lifecycle-entry-point-initializat | critical | platform-replaced | platform-replaced | app/build.gradle.kts | HarmonyOS replaces those Android build features with EntryAbility startup hooks, FoodikeBootstrap page loading, and stage-mode module registration. |\n105: | app-build-gradle-kts-aa010bdd3d-005-settings-preferences-option-toggles-or-c | critical | platform-replaced | platform-replaced | app/build.gradle.kts | HarmonyOS replaces DataStore with LoginPreferencesService backed by ArkData Preferences for persisted login-state storage. |\n106: | build-gradle-kts-e6afb1cfd2-001-runtime-permission-request-permission-re | critical | planned | unverified | build.gradle.kts |  |\n107: | build-gradle-kts-6cd8a326ab-002-android-platform-component-lifecycle-suc | critical | planned | unverified | build.gradle.kts |  |\n108: | build-gradle-kts-2f9b07ef27-003-settings-preferences-option-toggles-or-c | critical | planned | unverified | build.gradle.kts |  |\n109: | readme-md-44b694e8e8-001-file-document-storage-saf-mediastore-or | critical | planned | unverified | README.md |  |\n110: | readme-md-fabca22af6-002-image-viewing-bitmap-exif-handling-zoom | critical | planned | unverified | README.md |  |\n111: | readme-md-d2eb97d44e-003-navigation-surface-menu-drawer-toolbar-o | critical | planned | unverified | README.md |  |\n112: | readme-md-2508cec37d-004-runtime-permission-request-permission-re | critical | planned | unverified | README.md |  |\n113: | readme-md-d602d28d83-005-android-platform-component-lifecycle-suc | critical | planned | unverified | README.md |  |\n114: | readme-md-6721045c2d-006-screen-lifecycle-entry-point-initializat | critical | planned | unverified | README.md |  |\n115: | readme-md-449a470b45-007-observable-state-viewmodel-flow-livedata | critical | planned | unverified | README.md |  |\n116: | app-src-main-androidmanifest-xml-e5fadea668-001-android-resource-configuration-must-be-m | critical | implemented | equivalent | app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml | HarmonyOS app and module descriptors map bundle label/icon/version and start-window resources through AppScope/app.json5, entry/src/main/module.json5, and base string/color resources. |\n117: | app-src-main-androidmanifest-xml-525ca85433-002-intent-uri-bundle-deeplink-or-cross-scre | critical | platform-replaced | platform-replaced | app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml | HarmonyOS entry/src/main/module.json5 exposes the launcher entry ability through home action/entity skills, and app_router.cj continues startup into named in-app routes. |\n118: | app-src-main-androidmanifest-xml-dcc4612e71-003-runtime-permission-request-permission-re | critical | not-applicable | not-applicable | app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml | HarmonyOS entry module keeps requestPermissions em